<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Tenth session  
Agenda item 3 
</p>
<p><b>PROMOTION AND PROTECTION OF ALL HUMAN RIGHTS, 
CIVIL, POLITICAL, ECONOMIC, SOCIAL AND CULTURAL 
    RIGHTS, INCLUDING THE RIGHT TO DEVELOPMENT 
</b></p>
<p><b>Angola, Austria</b>*,<b> Bolivia, Brazil, Burkina Faso, Cameroon, Chile, Colombia</b>*,<b> 
Costa Rica</b>*,<b> Cuba, Ecuador</b>*,<b> Egypt, Finland</b>*,<b> Guatemala</b>*<b>, Italy, Morocco</b>*,<b> 
Netherlands, Nicaragua, Palestine</b>*,<b> Panama</b>*,<b> Peru</b>*,<b> Philippines, Portugal</b>*,<b> 
Republic of the Congo</b>*,<b> Slovakia, South Africa, Spain</b>*,<b> Tunisia</b>*,<b> Ukraine, 
            Uruguay, Venezuela (Bolivarian Republic of):  draft resolution 
</b></p>
<p><b>10/&#8230; Draft United Nations guidelines for the appropriate  
use and conditions of alternative care for children 
</b></p>
<p><i> The Human Rights Council</i>, </p>
<p> <i>Reaffirming</i> the Universal Declaration of Human Rights and the Convention on the Rights 
of the Child, and celebrating the twentieth anniversary of the Convention in 2009, 
</p>
<p>                                                 
</p>
<p>*  Non-member State of the Human Rights Council. </p>

 <p></p>
<p> <i>Reaffirming also</i> all previous Council resolutions on the rights of the child of the Council, 
the Commission on Human Right and the General Assembly, the most recent being Council 
resolutions 7/29 of 28 March 2008 and 9/13 of 24 September 2008 and General Assembly 
resolution 63/241 of 23 December 2008, 
</p>
<p><i> Welcomes</i> the progress made during consultations on the draft United Nations guidelines 
for the appropriate use and conditions of alternative care for children and decides to continue 
efforts to take action on them at its eleventh session. 
</p>
